Residues of pesticides and veterinary drugs, as well as presence of heavy metals in food, threatens our safety and health. Unsatisfactory (due to the presence of harmful admixtures) food supplies also cause substantial economic losses. Thus, rapid assessment of food safety is needed, and nanomaterials are very promising candidates to help scientists and engineers to achieve this goal (Fig. 6
                         and Table 1
                        ).
